Anonymous Fri 10 Feb 2023 21:44:03 No.54338447 Report
Quoted By:
>>54336705
>prompt with numbers and weights
worry about sampler, steps, cfg, and denoise for img2img

sampler: there's like 20 of them and each will be a little different but if you run one thing through all of them you'll usually get five or six groups that are the same except for fine detail so figure out which ones give stuff you like without being mangled too badly

steps: start at 10 and try adding 3 at a time. some samplers will give garbage unless they get a lot of steps but most will do something useful in 10 to 30, and some samplers will give different poses at different steps.

cfg: start low, even 3 or 4 can look good and the higher you go the more chance it'll look bad because it's trying to hard to apply keywords to shapes in the picture that aren't the part you wanted that word to put in the image

denoise: this is like how much it can redraw the image you gave it, lower than .25 it can't change enough to do more than mutilate the sauce, over .75 it will do whatever it wants

also, a lot of things can be fixed and refined with inpaint using different keywords, samplers, and little tweaks without copy pasting a hundred keywords that SD doesn't know much about or find in the models
